Brett+Lyons+Design+and+Analysis+Engineer+CL+and+Resume,[u'OBJECTIVE ', u'RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE ', u'SKILLS  ', u'EDUCATION ', u'Related Coursework  ']","<?xml version=""1.0"" encoding=""UTF-8""?>
<page number=""1"" position=""absolute"" top=""0"" left=""0"" height=""1188"" width=""918"">
<text top=""84"" left=""135"" width=""80"" height=""15"" font=""0"">Brett Lyons </text>
<text top=""120"" left=""135"" width=""88"" height=""15"" font=""0"">584 Main St. </text>
<text top=""138"" left=""135"" width=""134"" height=""15"" font=""0"">Portland, CT 06480 </text>
<text top=""210"" left=""135"" width=""135"" height=""15"" font=""0"">Dear Sir or Madam: </text>
<text top=""246"" left=""189"" width=""592"" height=""15"" font=""0"">I would like to express my interest in a Design and Analysis Engineering position through </text>
<text top=""264"" left=""135"" width=""613"" height=""15"" font=""0"">Monroe Staffing. You will note from my enclosed résumé that I am currently employed as an </text>
<text top=""282"" left=""135"" width=""652"" height=""15"" font=""0"">Engineering Intern at TurboVision Consulting Group, Inc. TurboVision is an established consulting </text>
<text top=""300"" left=""135"" width=""607"" height=""15"" font=""0"">group contracted by several major industrial gas turbine manufacturers including Mitsubishi </text>
<text top=""318"" left=""135"" width=""625"" height=""15"" font=""0"">Heavy Industries and Kawasaki Heavy Industries. Composed entirely of senior engineers with </text>
<text top=""336"" left=""135"" width=""630"" height=""15"" font=""0"">over 30 years of experience, their focus is on taking the expertise and knowledge developed in </text>
<text top=""354"" left=""135"" width=""635"" height=""15"" font=""0"">the highly rigorous design of jet engines and applying it to the industrial turbomachinery setting. </text>
<text top=""372"" left=""135"" width=""639"" height=""15"" font=""0"">Working alongside these senior engineers I have been helping to develop their new approach to </text>
<text top=""390"" left=""135"" width=""648"" height=""15"" font=""0"">multistage axial compressor airfoil design intended to reduce overall development time compared </text>
<text top=""408"" left=""135"" width=""355"" height=""15"" font=""0"">to current aero-engine compressor design practices.  </text>
<text top=""426"" left=""189"" width=""579"" height=""15"" font=""0"">Over the past year and a half I have worked on multiple projects, including validation of </text>
<text top=""444"" left=""135"" width=""602"" height=""15"" font=""0"">our in-house CFD software and airfoil incidence range modeling. In my main project I have </text>
<text top=""462"" left=""135"" width=""577"" height=""15"" font=""0"">designed a preliminary analysis system to quickly and automatically create, mesh, and </text>
<text top=""480"" left=""135"" width=""629"" height=""15"" font=""0"">structurally analyze rotor and stator CAD models using two open-source software applications, </text>
<text top=""498"" left=""135"" width=""646"" height=""15"" font=""0"">GMSH and CalculiX. GMSH is a three-dimensional finite element mesh generator and CalculiX is </text>
<text top=""516"" left=""135"" width=""637"" height=""15"" font=""0"">a finite element analysis application with ABAQUS-style input formatting used by both MTU and </text>
<text top=""534"" left=""135"" width=""637"" height=""15"" font=""0"">the DLR. The primary goal of this project is to use the preliminary analysis system to reduce the </text>
<text top=""552"" left=""135"" width=""649"" height=""15"" font=""0"">overall design time. The projectʼs secondary goal is to test the accuracy and reliability of the open </text>
<text top=""570"" left=""135"" width=""639"" height=""15"" font=""0"">source software for use in a final structural analysis system in order to reduce the overall project </text>
<text top=""588"" left=""135"" width=""421"" height=""15"" font=""0"">costs associated with getting a license for other FEA software.  </text>
<text top=""606"" left=""189"" width=""575"" height=""15"" font=""0"">After receiving my Aerospace Engineering degree from Boston University and working </text>
<text top=""624"" left=""135"" width=""638"" height=""15"" font=""0"">diligently as an aerospace engineer, I now possess the skill set and dedication to be an asset to </text>
<text top=""642"" left=""135"" width=""612"" height=""15"" font=""0"">your company. During my time at TurboVision I have quickly learned to work with many new </text>
<text top=""660"" left=""135"" width=""627"" height=""15"" font=""0"">software programs, including neural networking and finite element analysis applications. In my </text>
<text top=""678"" left=""135"" width=""638"" height=""15"" font=""0"">work designing an automated system to fully mesh and analyze the stress and modal frequency </text>
<text top=""696"" left=""135"" width=""616"" height=""15"" font=""0"">response of compressor rotor blades and stator vanes, I have learned to work independently </text>
<text top=""714"" left=""135"" width=""650"" height=""15"" font=""0"">while consulting with senior engineers. At Boston University, I had the opportunity to take courses </text>
